---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import StoryStep from '../StoryStep.astro';
import Canvas from '../Canvas.astro';
import Item from '../Item.astro';
import outkast from '../../assets/sounds-of-atlanta/outkast.png';
import tlc from '../../assets/sounds-of-atlanta/tlc.png';
import braxton from '../../assets/sounds-of-atlanta/braxton.png';
---

<StoryStep title="Sounds of Atlanta" mediaFirst>
	<!-- Free-flow pocket: drag/resize/rotate these with ?edit. -->
	<Canvas slot="media" fill fitScale class="cluster">
		<!-- DOM order = back → front: tlc, braxton, outkast (front) -->
		<Item
			left="44.8%"
			top="-3.7%"
			width="55.6%"
			phone={{ left: '37.3%', top: '3.2%', width: '55.3%', rotate: 0 }}
		>
			<Image src={tlc} alt="TLC" />
		</Item>
		<Item
			left="1.4%"
			top="4.6%"
			width="35.7%"
			rotate={-3.4}
			phone={{ left: '15.3%', top: '4.5%', width: '35.7%', rotate: -3.4 }}
		>
			<Image src={braxton} alt="Toni Braxton" />
		</Item>
		<Item
			left="13.3%"
			top="36.9%"
			width="69.6%"
			phone={{ left: '16.2%', top: '37%', width: '69.6%', rotate: 0 }}
		>
			<Image src={outkast} alt="OutKast" />
		</Item>
	</Canvas>

	<div class="copy">
		<p>
			Atlanta always had the roots—the gospel, the churches, the Auburn Avenue
			clubs. But it was never a music capital.
		</p>
		<p>
			Then came the 90s. OutKast rewrote what rap could be. TLC became the best-selling girl group in American history. Toni Braxton turned LaFace Records into an R&B empire.
		</p>
	</div>
</StoryStep>

<style>
	/* breathing room below the body text, before the prev/next bar */
	.copy {
		padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}
	/* more gap between the canvas and the copy on phone */
	:global(:root[data-bp='phone']) .copy {
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}
</style>
